This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with enhancing the resolution of MRI images using machine learning techniques. The use of random forest regression and customized features also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of efficiency for model training and inference suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of a single or handful of volumes for training data suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
